<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Numbers 21:1-35</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="35">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Now the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ite the king of A&acute;rad, who dwelt in the Neg&acute;eb, got to hear that Israel had come by the way of Ath&acute;a&middot;rim, and he began to fight with Israel and carry away some of them as captives.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Consequently Israel made a vow to Jehovah and said: “If you will without fail give this people into my hand, I shall also certainly devote their cities to destruction.”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">So Jehovah listened to Israel’s voice and gave the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ites over; and they devoted them and their cities to destruction. Hence they called the name of the place Hor&acute;mah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">While they continued trekking from Mount Hor by the way of the Red Sea to go around the land of E&acute;dom, the soul of the people began tiring out because of the way.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And the people kept speaking against God and Moses: “Why have <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For there is no bread and no water, and our soul has come to abhor the contemptible bread.”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So Jehovah sent poisonous serpents among the people, and they kept biting the people, so that many people of Israel died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Finally the people came to Moses and said: “We have sinned, because we have spoken against Jehovah and against you. Intercede with Jehovah that he may remove the serpents from upon us.” And Moses went interceding in behalf of the people.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Then Jehovah said to Moses: “Make for yourself a fiery snake and place it upon a signal pole. And it must occur that when anyone has been bitten, he then has to look at it and so must keep alive.”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Moses at once made a serpent of copper and placed it upon the signal pole; and it did occur that if a serpent had bitten a man and he gazed at the copper serpent, he then kept alive.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">After that the sons of Israel pulled away and encamped in O&acute;both.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Then they pulled away from O&acute;both and encamped in I&acute;ye-ab&acute;a&middot;rim, in the wilderness that is toward the front of Mo&acute;ab, toward the rising of the sun.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">From there they pulled away and took up camping by the torrent valley of Ze&acute;red.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">From there they pulled away and went camping in the region of the Ar&acute;non, which is in the wilderness that extends from the border of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites; for the Ar&acute;non is the boundary of Mo&acute;ab, between Mo&acute;ab and the Am&acute;or&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">That is why it is said in the book of the Wars of Jehovah:</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs14-2">“Va&acute;heb in Su&acute;phah and the torrent valleys of Ar&acute;non,</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">and the mouth of the torrent valleys, which has bent itself toward the seat of Ar and has leaned against the border of Mo&acute;ab.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Next from there on to Be&acute;er. This is the well about which Jehovah said to Moses: “Gather the people, and let me give them water.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">At that time Israel proceeded to sing this song:<br><span class="p">“Spring up, O well! Respond to it, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> people!</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">A well, princes dug it. The nobles of the people excavated it,<br><span class="z">With a commander’s staff, with their own staffs.”</span></span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs18-3">Then from the wilderness on to Mat&acute;ta&middot;nah.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And from Mat&acute;ta&middot;nah on to Na&middot;hal&acute;i&middot;el, and from Na&middot;hal&acute;i&middot;el on to Ba&acute;moth.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And from Ba&acute;moth on to the valley that is in the field of Mo&acute;ab, at the head of Pis&acute;gah, and it projects over toward the face of Je&middot;shi&acute;mon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Israel now sent messengers to Si&acute;hon the king of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, saying:</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">“Let me pass through your land. We shall not turn off into a field or a vineyard. We shall drink water of no well. On the king’s road we shall march until we pass through your territory.”</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And Si&acute;hon did not allow Israel to pass through his territory, but Si&acute;hon gathered all his people and went out to meet Israel in the wilderness, and came to Ja&acute;haz and began fighting with Israel.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">At that Israel struck him with the edge of the sword and took possession of his land from the Ar&acute;non to the Jab&acute;bok, near the sons of Am&acute;mon; because Ja&acute;zer is the border of the sons of Am&acute;mon.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">So Israel took all these cities, and Israel began dwelling in all the cities of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, in Hesh&acute;bon and all its dependent towns.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">For Hesh&acute;bon was the city of Si&acute;hon. He was the king of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, and it was he who fought with the king of Mo&acute;ab formerly and went taking all his land out of his hand as far as the Ar&acute;non.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">That is why the sayers of mock verses would say:</span>
</p>

<p class="p"> 
       <span id="vs27-2">“Come to Hesh&acute;bon.<br><span class="z">Let the city of Si&acute;hon be built and be proved firmly set up.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">For a fire has come out of Hesh&acute;bon, a flame from the town of Si&acute;hon.<br><span class="z">It has consumed Ar of Mo&acute;ab, the owners of the high places of the Ar&acute;non.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Woe to you, Mo&acute;ab! You will certainly perish, O people of Che&acute;mosh!<br><span class="z">He will certainly give his sons as escaped ones and his daughters in the captivity to the king of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, Si&acute;hon.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">So let us shoot at them.<br><span class="z">Hesh&acute;bon will certainly perish up to Di&acute;bon,</span><br><span class="z">And the women up to No&acute;phah, the men up to Med&acute;e&middot;ba.”</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And Israel began to dwell in the land of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">Then Moses sent some to spy on Ja&acute;zer. So they captured its dependent towns and dispossessed the Am&acute;or&middot;ites who were there.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">After that they turned and went up by the way of Ba&acute;shan. At this Og the king of Ba&acute;shan came out to meet them, he and all his people, to the battle of Ed&acute;re&middot;i.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Jehovah now said to Moses: “Do not be afraid of him, for into your hand I shall certainly give him and all his people and his land; and you must do to him just as you did to Si&acute;hon, the king of the Am&acute;or&middot;ites, who used to dwell in Hesh&acute;bon.”</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">So they went striking him and his sons and all his people, until there was no survivor remaining to him; and they went taking possession of his land.</span>
</p>
</form>

<script language="JavaScript1.2" type="text/javascript">
