<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Numbers 22:1-41</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="41">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">Then the sons of Israel pulled away and encamped on the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab across the Jordan from Jer&acute;i&middot;cho.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And Ba&acute;lak the son of Zip&acute;por got to see all that Israel had done to the Am&acute;or&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Mo&acute;ab became very frightened at the people, because they were many; and Mo&acute;ab began to feel a sickening dread of the sons of Israel.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And Mo&acute;ab proceeded to say to the older men of Mid&acute;i&middot;an: “Now this congregation will lick up all our surroundings like the bull licking up the green growth of the field.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs4-2">And Ba&acute;lak the son of Zip&acute;por was king of Mo&acute;ab at that particular time.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">He now sent messengers to Ba&acute;laam the son of Be&acute;or at Pe&acute;thor, which is by the River of the land of the sons of his people, to call him, saying: “Look! A people has come out of Egypt. Look! They have covered the earth as far as one can see, and they are dwelling right in front of me.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And now do come, please; do curse this people for me, for they are mightier than I am. Perhaps I may be able to strike them and I may drive them out of the land; for I well know that the one whom you bless is a blessed one and the one whom you curse is cursed.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">So the older men of Mo&acute;ab and the older men of Mid&acute;i&middot;an traveled with the payments for divination in their hands and went to Ba&acute;laam and spoke to him Ba&acute;lak’s words.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">At that he said to them: “Lodge here tonight, and I shall certainly return <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> word just as Jehovah may speak to me.” Accordingly the princes of Mo&acute;ab stayed with Ba&acute;laam.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Then God came to Ba&acute;laam and said: “Who are these men with you?”</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">So Ba&acute;laam said to the [true] God: “Ba&acute;lak the son of Zip&acute;por, the king of Mo&acute;ab, has sent to me, saying,</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">‘Look! The people who are coming out of Egypt, and they go covering the earth as far as the eye can see. Now do come, do execrate them for me. Perhaps I may be able to fight against them and I shall actually drive them out.’”</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">But God said to Ba&acute;laam: “You must not go with them. You must not curse the people, for they are blessed.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">After that Ba&acute;laam got up in the morning and said to the princes of Ba&acute;lak: “Go to <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> country, because Jehovah has refused to let me go with <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>.”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">So the princes of Mo&acute;ab got up and came to Ba&acute;lak and said: “Ba&acute;laam has refused to come with us.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">However, Ba&acute;lak sent again other princes in greater number and more honorable than the former.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">In turn they came to Ba&acute;laam and said to him: “This is what Ba&acute;lak the son of Zip&acute;por has said, ‘Do not be detained, please, from coming to me.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">For I shall without fail honor you greatly, and everything you may say to me I shall do. So do come, please. Do execrate this people for me.’”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">But Ba&acute;laam answered and said to the servants of Ba&acute;lak: “If Ba&acute;lak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I should not be able to pass beyond the order of Jehovah my God, so as to do something small or great.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And now <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men also stay here, please, tonight that I may know what further Jehovah will speak with me.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">Then God came to Ba&acute;laam by night and said to him: “If it is to call you that the men have come, get up, go with them. But only the word that I shall speak to you is what you may speak.”</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">After that Ba&acute;laam got up in the morning and saddled his she-ass and went with the princes of Mo&acute;ab.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And the anger of God began to blaze because he was going; and Jehovah’s angel proceeded to station himself in the road to resist him. And he was riding upon his she-ass, and two attendants of his were with him.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">And the ass got to see Jehovah’s angel stationed in the road with his drawn sword in his hand; and the ass tried to turn aside from the road that she might go into the field, but Ba&acute;laam began to strike the ass in order to turn her aside to the road.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And Jehovah’s angel kept standing in the narrow way between the vineyards, with a stone wall on this side and a stone wall on that side.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">And the she-ass kept seeing Jehovah’s angel and began to squeeze herself against the wall and so to squeeze Ba&acute;laam’s foot against the wall; and he went beating her some more.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Jehovah’s angel now passed by again and stood in a narrow place, where there was no way to turn aside to the right or the left.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">When the ass got to see Jehovah’s angel she now lay down under Ba&acute;laam; so that Ba&acute;laam’s anger blazed, and he kept beating the ass with his staff.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Finally Jehovah opened the mouth of the ass and she said to Ba&acute;laam: “What have I done to you so that you have beaten me these three times?”</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">At this Ba&acute;laam said to the ass: “It is because you have dealt ruthlessly with me. If only there were a sword in my hand, for now I should have killed you!”</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Then the she-ass said to Ba&acute;laam: “Am I not your she-ass that you have ridden upon all your life long until this day? Have I ever been used to do to you this way?” To which he said: “No!”</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And Jehovah proceeded to uncover Ba&acute;laam’s eyes, so that he saw Jehovah’s angel stationed in the road with his drawn sword in his hand. At once he bowed low and prostrated himself on his face.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">Then Jehovah’s angel said to him: “Why have you beaten your she-ass these three times? Look! I—I have come out to offer resistance, because your way has been headlong against my will.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And the she-ass got to see me and tried to turn aside before me these three times. Supposing she had not turned aside from before me! For by now even you I should have killed, but her I should have preserved alive.”</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">At this Ba&acute;laam said to Jehovah’s angel: “I have sinned, because I did not know that it was you stationed in the road to meet me. And now, if it is bad in your eyes, let me go my way back.”</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">But Jehovah’s angel said to Ba&acute;laam: “Go with the men; and nothing but the word that I shall speak to you is what you may speak.” And Ba&acute;laam continued going with the princes of Ba&acute;lak.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">When Ba&acute;lak got to hear that Ba&acute;laam had come, he at once went out to meet him at the city of Mo&acute;ab, which is on the bank of the Ar&acute;non, which is on the extremity of the territory.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Then Ba&acute;lak said to Ba&acute;laam: “Have I not for a fact sent to you to call you? Why did you not come to me? Am I not really and truly able to honor you?”</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">At this Ba&acute;laam said to Ba&acute;lak: “Here I have come to you now. Shall I be able at all to speak something? The word that God will place in my mouth is what I shall speak.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">So Ba&acute;laam went with Ba&acute;lak and they came to Kir&acute;i&middot;ath-hu&acute;zoth.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">And Ba&acute;lak proceeded to sacrifice cattle and sheep and to send some to Ba&acute;laam and the princes who were with him.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">And it came about in the morning that Ba&acute;lak went taking Ba&acute;laam and bringing him up to Ba&acute;moth-ba&acute;al, that he might see from there the whole of the people.</span>
</p>
</form>

