<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Numbers 26:1-65</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="65">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about after the scourge, that Jehovah went on to say this to Moses and El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the son of Aaron the priest:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“T<span class="smallcaps">AKE</span> the sum of the whole assembly of the sons of Israel from twenty years of age and upward, according to the house of their fathers, all those going out to the army in Israel.”</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Moses and El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the priest proceeded to speak with them in the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab by the Jordan at Jer&acute;i&middot;cho, saying:</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">“[Take the sum of them] from the age of twenty years and upward, just as Jehovah had commanded Moses.”</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs4-2">Now the sons of Israel who went out of the land of Egypt were:</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">Reu&acute;ben, Israel’s firstborn; Reu&acute;ben’s sons: Of Ha&acute;noch the family of the Ha&acute;noch&middot;ites; of Pal&acute;lu the family of the Pal&acute;lu&middot;ites;</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">of Hez&acute;ron the family of the Hez&acute;ron&middot;ites; of Car&acute;mi the family of the Car&acute;mites.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">These were the families of the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites, and their registered ones amounted to forty-three thousand seven hundred and thirty.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">And the son of Pal&acute;lu was E&middot;li&acute;ab.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And the sons of E&middot;li&acute;ab: Nem&acute;u&middot;el and Da&acute;than and A&middot;bi&acute;ram. This Da&acute;than and A&middot;bi&acute;ram were summoned ones of the assembly, who engaged in a struggle against Moses and Aaron in the assembly of Ko&acute;rah, when they engaged in a struggle against Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Then the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up. As for Ko&acute;rah, [he died] at the death of the assembly when the fire consumed two hundred and fifty men. And they came to be a symbol.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">However, the sons of Ko&acute;rah did not die.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">The sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on by their families: Of Nem&acute;u&middot;el the family of the Nem&acute;u&middot;el&middot;ites; of Ja&acute;min the family of the Ja&acute;min&middot;ites; of Ja&acute;chin the family of the Ja&acute;chin&middot;ites;</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">of Ze&acute;rah the family of the Ze&acute;rah&middot;ites; of Sha&acute;ul the family of the Sha&middot;u&acute;lites.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">These were the families of the Sim&acute;e&middot;on&middot;ites: twenty-two thousand two hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">The sons of Gad by their families: Of Ze&acute;phon the family of the Ze&acute;phon&middot;ites; of Hag&acute;gi the family of the Hag&acute;gites; of Shu&acute;ni the family of the Shu&acute;nites;</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">of Oz&acute;ni the family of the Oz&acute;nites; of E&acute;ri the family of the E&acute;rites;</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">of Ar&acute;od the family of the Ar&acute;od&middot;ites; of A&middot;re&acute;li the family of the A&middot;re&acute;lites.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">These were the families of the sons of Gad, of their registered ones: forty thousand five hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">The sons of Judah were Er and O&acute;nan. However, Er and O&acute;nan died in the land of Ca&acute;naan.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And the sons of Judah came to be, by their families: Of She&acute;lah the family of the She&middot;la&acute;nites; of Pe&acute;rez the family of the Per&acute;e&middot;zites; of Ze&acute;rah the family of the Ze&acute;rah&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And the sons of Pe&acute;rez came to be: Of Hez&acute;ron the family of the Hez&acute;ron&middot;ites; of Ha&acute;mul the family of the Ha&middot;mu&acute;lites.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">These were the families of Judah, of their registered ones: seventy-six thousand five hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">The sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char by their families were: Of To&acute;la the family of the To&acute;la&middot;ites; of Pu&acute;vah the family of the Pu&acute;nites;</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">of Ja&acute;shub the family of the Jash&acute;u&middot;bites; of Shim&acute;ron the family of the Shim&acute;ron&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">These were the families of Is&acute;sa&middot;char, of their registered ones: sixty-four thousand three hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">The sons of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun by their families were: Of Se&acute;red the family of the Ser&acute;e&middot;dites; of E&acute;lon the family of the E&acute;lon&middot;ites; of Jah&acute;le&middot;el the family of the Jah&acute;le&middot;el&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">These were the families of the Ze&middot;bu&acute;lu&middot;nites, of their registered ones: sixty thousand five hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">The sons of Joseph by their families were Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh and E&acute;phra&middot;im.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">The sons of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh were: Of Ma&acute;chir the family of the Ma&acute;chir&middot;ites. And Ma&acute;chir became father to Gil&acute;e&middot;ad. Of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad the family of the Gil&acute;e&middot;ad&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">These were the sons of Gil&acute;e&middot;ad: Of Ie&acute;zer the family of the Ie&acute;zer&middot;ites; of He&acute;lek the family of the He&acute;lek&middot;ites;</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">of As&acute;ri&middot;el the family of the As&acute;ri&middot;el&middot;ites; of She&acute;chem the family of the She&acute;chem&middot;ites;</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">of She&middot;mi&acute;da the family of the She&middot;mi&acute;da&middot;ites; of He&acute;pher the family of the He&acute;pher&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Now Ze&middot;lo&acute;phe&middot;had the son of He&acute;pher proved to have no sons, but daughters, and the names of the daughters of Ze&middot;lo&acute;phe&middot;had were Mah&acute;lah and Noah, Hog&acute;lah, Mil&acute;cah and Tir&acute;zah.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">These were the families of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh, and their registered ones were fifty-two thousand seven hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">These were the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im by their families: Of Shu&acute;the&middot;lah the family of the Shu&acute;thel&middot;a&acute;hites; of Be&acute;cher the family of the Be&acute;cher&middot;ites; of Ta&acute;han the family of the Ta&acute;han&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And these were the sons of Shu&acute;the&middot;lah: Of E&acute;ran the family of the E&acute;ran&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">These were the families of the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im, of their registered ones: thirty-two thousand five hundred. These were the sons of Joseph by their families.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">The sons of Benjamin by their families were: Of Be&acute;la the family of the Be&acute;la&middot;ites; of Ash&acute;bel the family of the Ash&acute;bel&middot;ites; of A&middot;hi&acute;ram the family of the A&middot;hi&acute;ram&middot;ites;</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">of She&middot;phu&acute;pham the family of the Shu&acute;pham&middot;ites; of Hu&acute;pham the family of the Hu&acute;pham&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">The sons of Be&acute;la came to be Ard and Na&acute;a&middot;man: [Of Ard] the family of the Ard&acute;ites; of Na&acute;a&middot;man the family of the Na&acute;a&middot;mites.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">These were the sons of Benjamin by their families, and their registered ones were forty-five thousand six hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">These were the sons of Dan by their families: Of Shu&acute;ham the family of the Shu&acute;ham&middot;ites. These were the families of Dan by their families.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">All the families of the Shu&acute;ham&middot;ites, of their registered ones, were sixty-four thousand four hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">The sons of Ash&acute;er by their families were: Of Im&acute;nah the family of the Im&acute;nites; of Ish&acute;vi the family of the Ish&acute;vites; of Be&middot;ri&acute;ah the family of the Be&middot;ri&acute;ites;</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">of the sons of Be&middot;ri&acute;ah: Of He&acute;ber the family of the He&acute;ber&middot;ites; of Mal&acute;chi&middot;el the family of the Mal&acute;chi&middot;el&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">And the name of Ash&acute;er’s daughter was Se&acute;rah.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">These were the families of the sons of Ash&acute;er, of their registered ones: fifty-three thousand four hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">The sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li by their families were: Of Jah&acute;ze&middot;el the family of the Jah&acute;ze&middot;el&middot;ites; of Gu&acute;ni the family of the Gu&acute;nites;</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">of Je&acute;zer the family of the Je&acute;zer&middot;ites; of Shil&acute;lem the family of the Shil&acute;lem&middot;ites.</span> <a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">These were the families of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li by their families, and their registered ones were forty-five thousand four hundred.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">These were the registered ones of the sons of Israel: six hundred and one thousand seven hundred and thirty.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">After that Jehovah spoke to Moses, saying:</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">“To these the land should be apportioned for an inheritance by the number of the names.</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">According to the great number you should increase one’s inheritance, and according to the fewness you should reduce one’s inheritance. Each one’s inheritance should be given in proportion to his registered ones.</span> <a name="bk55" class="vsAnchor">55</a>
       <span id="vs55">Only by the lot should the land be apportioned. According to the names of the tribes of their fathers they should get an inheritance.</span> <a name="bk56" class="vsAnchor">56</a>
       <span id="vs56">By the determination of the lot one’s inheritance should be apportioned between the many and the few.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk57" class="vsAnchor">57</a>
       <span id="vs57">Now these were the registered ones of the Levites by their families: Of Ger&acute;shon the family of the Ger&acute;shon&middot;ites; of Ko&acute;hath the family of the Ko&acute;hath&middot;ites; of Me&middot;rar&acute;i the family of the Me&middot;rar&acute;ites.</span> <a name="bk58" class="vsAnchor">58</a>
       <span id="vs58">These were the families of the Levites: the family of the Lib&acute;nites, the family of the He&acute;bron&middot;ites, the family of the Mah&acute;lites, the family of the Mu&acute;shites, the family of the Ko&acute;rah&middot;ites.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs58-2">And Ko&acute;hath became father to Am&acute;ram.</span> <a name="bk59" class="vsAnchor">59</a>
       <span id="vs59">And the name of Am&acute;ram’s wife was Joch&acute;e&middot;bed, Le&acute;vi’s daughter, whom his wife bore to Le&acute;vi in Egypt. In time she bore to Am&acute;ram Aaron and Moses and Mir&acute;i&middot;am their sister.</span> <a name="bk60" class="vsAnchor">60</a>
       <span id="vs60">Then there were born to Aaron Na&acute;dab and A&middot;bi&acute;hu, El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar and Ith&acute;a&middot;mar.</span> <a name="bk61" class="vsAnchor">61</a>
       <span id="vs61">But Na&acute;dab and A&middot;bi&acute;hu died for their presenting illegitimate fire before Jehovah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk62" class="vsAnchor">62</a>
       <span id="vs62">And their registered ones amounted to twenty-three thousand, all males from a month old and upward. For they did not get registered in among the sons of Israel, because no inheritance was to be given to them in among the sons of Israel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk63" class="vsAnchor">63</a>
       <span id="vs63">These were the ones registered by Moses and El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the priest when they registered the sons of Israel in the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab by the Jordan at Jer&acute;i&middot;cho.</span> <a name="bk64" class="vsAnchor">64</a>
       <span id="vs64">But among these there did not prove to be a man of those registered by Moses and Aaron the priest when they registered the sons of Israel in the wilderness of Si&acute;nai.</span> <a name="bk65" class="vsAnchor">65</a>
       <span id="vs65">For Jehovah had said concerning them: “They will die without fail in the wilderness.” So there was not left of them a man except Ca&acute;leb the son of Je&middot;phun&acute;neh and Joshua the son of Nun.</span>
</p>
</form>

