<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Numbers 33:1-56</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="56">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">These were the stages of the sons of Israel who went out of the land of Egypt in their armies by the hand of Moses and Aaron.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">And Moses kept recording the departure places by their stages at the order of Jehovah; and these were their stages from one departure place to another:</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And they proceeded to pull away from Ram&acute;e&middot;ses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month. Directly the day after the passover the sons of Israel went out with uplifted hand before the eyes of all the Egyptians.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">All the while the Egyptians were burying those whom Jehovah had struck among them, that is, all the firstborn; and upon their gods Jehovah had executed judgments.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">So the sons of Israel pulled away from Ram&acute;e&middot;ses and went camping in Suc&acute;coth.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Then they pulled away from Suc&acute;coth and went camping in E&acute;tham, which is on the edge of the wilderness.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Next they pulled away from E&acute;tham and turned back toward Pi&middot;ha&middot;hi&acute;roth, which is in view of Ba&acute;al-ze&acute;phon; and they went camping before Mig&acute;dol.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">After that they pulled away from Pi&middot;ha&middot;hi&acute;roth and went passing through the midst of the sea to the wilderness and kept marching a three-day journey in the wilderness of E&acute;tham and took up camping at Ma&acute;rah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Then they pulled away from Ma&acute;rah and came to E&acute;lim. Now in E&acute;lim there were twelve springs of water and seventy palm trees. So they camped there.</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Next they pulled away from E&acute;lim and went camping by the Red Sea.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">After that they pulled away from the Red Sea and took up camping in the wilderness of Sin.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Then they pulled away from the wilderness of Sin and went camping at Doph&acute;kah.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Later they pulled away from Doph&acute;kah and went camping at A&acute;lush.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">They next pulled away from A&acute;lush and went camping in Reph&acute;i&middot;dim. And there proved to be no water there for the people to drink.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">After that they pulled away from Reph&acute;i&middot;dim and went camping in the wilderness of Si&acute;nai.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Subsequently they pulled away from the wilderness of Si&acute;nai and went camping at Kib&acute;roth-hat&middot;ta&acute;a&middot;vah.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Then they pulled away from Kib&acute;roth-hat&middot;ta&acute;a&middot;vah and went camping in Ha&middot;ze&acute;roth.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">After that they pulled away from Ha&middot;ze&acute;roth and went camping in Rith&acute;mah.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">Next they pulled away from Rith&acute;mah and took up camping in Rim&acute;mon-pe&acute;rez.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">Then they pulled away from Rim&acute;mon-pe&acute;rez and went camping in Lib&acute;nah.</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Later they pulled away from Lib&acute;nah and went camping in Ris&acute;sah.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">Next they pulled away from Ris&acute;sah and went camping in Ke&middot;he&middot;la&acute;thah.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Then they pulled away from Ke&middot;he&middot;la&acute;thah and went camping in Mount She&acute;pher.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">After that they pulled away from Mount She&acute;pher and went camping in Har&middot;a&acute;dah.</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Then they pulled away from Har&middot;a&acute;dah and went camping in Mak&middot;he&acute;loth.</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Next they pulled away from Mak&middot;he&acute;loth and went camping in Ta&acute;hath.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">After that they pulled away from Ta&acute;hath and went camping in Te&acute;rah.</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">Then they pulled away from Te&acute;rah and went camping in Mith&acute;kah.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Later they pulled away from Mith&acute;kah and went camping in Hash&middot;mo&acute;nah.</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Next they pulled away from Hash&middot;mo&acute;nah and went camping in Mo&middot;se&acute;roth.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">Then they pulled away from Mo&middot;se&acute;roth and went camping in Ben&acute;e-ja&acute;a&middot;kan.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">After that they pulled away from Ben&acute;e-ja&acute;a&middot;kan and went camping in Hor-hag&middot;gid&acute;gad.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">Next they pulled away from Hor-hag&middot;gid&acute;gad and went camping in Jot&acute;ba&middot;thah.</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Later they pulled away from Jot&acute;ba&middot;thah and went camping in A&middot;bro&acute;nah.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Then they pulled away from A&middot;bro&acute;nah and went camping in E&acute;zi&middot;on-ge&acute;ber.</span> <a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">After that they pulled away from E&acute;zi&middot;on-ge&acute;ber and went camping in the wilderness of Zin, that is to say, Ka&acute;desh.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Later they pulled away from Ka&acute;desh and went camping in Mount Hor, on the frontier of the land of E&acute;dom.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">And Aaron the priest proceeded to go up into Mount Hor at the order of Jehovah and to die there in the fortieth year of the going out of the sons of Israel from the land of Egypt, in the fifth month, on the first of the month.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And Aaron was a hundred and twenty-three years old at his death on Mount Hor.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">Now the Ca&acute;naan&middot;ite, the king of A&acute;rad, as he was dwelling in the Neg&acute;eb, in the land of Ca&acute;naan, got to hear about the coming of the sons of Israel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">In time they pulled away from Mount Hor and went camping in Zal&middot;mo&acute;nah.</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">After that they pulled away from Zal&middot;mo&acute;nah and went camping in Pu&acute;non.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Next they pulled away from Pu&acute;non and went camping in O&acute;both.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">Then they pulled away from O&acute;both and went camping in I&acute;ye-ab&acute;a&middot;rim on the border of Mo&acute;ab.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">Later they pulled away from I&acute;yim and went camping in Di&acute;bon-gad.</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">After that they pulled away from Di&acute;bon-gad and went camping in Al&acute;mon-dib&middot;la&middot;tha&acute;im.</span> <a name="bk47" class="vsAnchor">47</a>
       <span id="vs47">Then they pulled away from Al&acute;mon-dib&middot;la&middot;tha&acute;im and went camping in the mountains of Ab&acute;a&middot;rim before Ne&acute;bo.</span> <a name="bk48" class="vsAnchor">48</a>
       <span id="vs48">Finally they pulled away from the mountains of Ab&acute;a&middot;rim and took up camping on the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab by the Jordan at Jer&acute;i&middot;cho.</span> <a name="bk49" class="vsAnchor">49</a>
       <span id="vs49">And they continued camping by the Jordan from Beth-jesh&acute;i&middot;moth to A&acute;bel-shit&acute;tim on the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk50" class="vsAnchor">50</a>
       <span id="vs50">And Jehovah proceeded to speak to Moses on the desert plains of Mo&acute;ab by the Jordan at Jer&acute;i&middot;cho, saying:</span> <a name="bk51" class="vsAnchor">51</a>
       <span id="vs51">“Speak to the sons of Israel, and you must say to them, ‘Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> are crossing the Jordan into the land of Ca&acute;naan.</span> <a name="bk52" class="vsAnchor">52</a>
       <span id="vs52">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must drive away all the inhabitants of the land from before <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> and destroy all their stone figures, and all their images of molten metal <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should destroy, and all their sacred high places <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should annihilate.</span> <a name="bk53" class="vsAnchor">53</a>
       <span id="vs53">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must take possession of the land and dwell in it, because to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> I shall certainly give the land to take possession of it.</span> <a name="bk54" class="vsAnchor">54</a>
       <span id="vs54">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must apportion the land to yourselves as a possession by lot according to <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> families. To the populous one <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should increase his inheritance, and to the sparse one <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should reduce his inheritance. To where the lot will come out for him, there it will become his. By the tribes of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> fathers <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should provide yourselves with landed property.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk55" class="vsAnchor">55</a>
       <span id="vs55">“‘If, though, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will not drive the inhabitants of the land away from before <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>, then those whom <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> leave of them will certainly become as pricks in <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> eyes and as thorns in <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> sides, and they will indeed harass <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> on the land in which <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will be dwelling.</span> <a name="bk56" class="vsAnchor">56</a>
       <span id="vs56">And it must occur that just as I had figured doing to them I shall do to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span>.’”</span>
</p>
</form>

