<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Numbers 34:1-29</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="36">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="29">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And Jehovah spoke further to Moses, saying:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“Command the sons of Israel, and you must say to them, ‘Y<span class="smallcaps">OU</span> are going into the land of Ca&acute;naan. This is the land that will fall to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> by inheritance, the land of Ca&acute;naan according to its boundaries.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">“‘And <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> south side must prove to be from the wilderness of Zin alongside E&acute;dom, and <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> south boundary must prove to be from the extremity of the Salt Sea on the east.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> boundary must change direction from the south of the ascent of A&middot;krab&acute;bim and cross over to Zin, and its termination must prove to be on the south of Ka&acute;desh-bar&acute;ne&middot;a; and it must go out to Ha&acute;zar-ad&acute;dar and pass over to Az&acute;mon.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And the boundary must change direction at Az&acute;mon to the torrent valley of Egypt, and its termination must prove to be at the Sea.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">“‘As for a west boundary, it must prove to be for <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> the Great Sea and the shoreland. This will become <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> west boundary.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">“‘Now this will become <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> north boundary: From the Great Sea <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will mark out to Mount Hor as a boundary for yourselves.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">From Mount Hor <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will mark out the boundary to the entering in of Ha&acute;math, and the termination of the boundary must prove to be at Ze&acute;dad.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And the boundary must go out to Ziph&acute;ron, and its termination must prove to be Ha&acute;zar-e&acute;nan. This will become <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> north boundary.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">“‘Then <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must mark for yourselves as <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> boundary on the east from Ha&acute;zar-e&acute;nan to She&acute;pham.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the boundary must go down from She&acute;pham to Rib&acute;lah on the east of A&acute;in, and the border must go down and strike upon the eastern slope of the sea of Chin&acute;ne&middot;reth.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And the border must go down to the Jordan, and its termination must prove to be the Salt Sea. This will become <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> land according to its boundaries all around.’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">So Moses commanded the sons of Israel, saying: “This is the land that <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will apportion to yourselves as a possession by lot, just as Jehovah has commanded to give to the nine and a half tribes.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">For the tribe of the sons of the Reu&acute;ben&middot;ites by the house of their fathers and the tribe of the sons of the Gad&acute;ites by the house of their fathers have already taken, and the half tribe of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh have already taken their inheritance.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">The two and a half tribes have already taken their inheritance from the region of the Jordan by Jer&acute;i&middot;cho eastward toward the sunrising.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And Jehovah spoke further to Moses, saying:</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">“These are the names of the men who will divide the land to <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> people for a possession, El&middot;e&middot;a&acute;zar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> will take one chieftain out of each tribe to divide the land for a possession.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And these are the names of the men: Of the tribe of Judah, Ca&acute;leb the son of Je&middot;phun&acute;neh;</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">and of the tribe of the sons of Sim&acute;e&middot;on, She&middot;mu&acute;el the son of Am&middot;mi&acute;hud;</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">of the tribe of Benjamin, E&middot;li&acute;dad the son of Chis&acute;lon;</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">and of the tribe of the sons of Dan a chieftain, Buk&acute;ki the son of Jog&acute;li;</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">of the sons of Joseph, of the tribe of the sons of Ma&middot;nas&acute;seh a chieftain, Han&acute;ni&middot;el the son of E&acute;phod;</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">and of the tribe of the sons of E&acute;phra&middot;im a chieftain, Kem&middot;u&acute;el the son of Shiph&acute;tan;</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">and of the tribe of the sons of Zeb&acute;u&middot;lun a chieftain, E&middot;li&middot;za&acute;phan the son of Par&acute;nach;</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">and of the tribe of the sons of Is&acute;sa&middot;char a chieftain, Pal&acute;ti&middot;el the son of Az&acute;zan;</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">and of the tribe of the sons of Ash&acute;er a chieftain, A&middot;hi&acute;hud the son of She&middot;lo&acute;mi;</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">and of the tribe of the sons of Naph&acute;ta&middot;li a chieftain, Ped&middot;ah&acute;el the son of Am&middot;mi&acute;hud.”</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">These are the ones whom Jehovah commanded to make the sons of Israel landholders in the land of Ca&acute;naan.</span>
</p>
</form>

